neutral.name: Neutral Space
neutral.desc: This space can be freely traversed and have no additional effects.

shop.name: Shop
shop.desc: A player who lands on this space receives a random item, if there is room in the player's inventory.

altar.name: Altar
altar.desc: A player on this space is allowed to make one wish. At the end of the turn, all players who made wishes have their wishes granted and then are returned to Start. Multiple players on this space do not engage in combat. Emits light level 5. In lieu of making a wish, a player who lands on this space can instead voluntarily be teleported to the Molten Core of the World at a random position.

start.name: Start Square
start.desc: All new players start on this square. Players sharing this space do not fight, and any player on this space does not lose HP for any reason. A player who ends his turn on Start is cured of any status ailments.

gap.name: Empty Gap
gap.desc: These spaces are ordinarily impassible to players. If a player is forced onto a gap, they immediately return to Start and loses 5 HP. A player who is adjacent to a gap can choose to leap into the gap.

black.name: Darkness
black.desc: A space shrouded in darkness; you can't tell what it is from this distance.

balloon.name: Balloon Space
balloon.visual: image of several balloons on a blue background
balloon.desc: This space summons a Balloon token on itself immediately, if it does not currently have a Balloon token on the board.

bush.name: Bush
bush.visual: light blue background with green bush texture

clouda.name: Small Cloud
clouda.visual: light blue background with small cloud
clouda.desc: A player who passes this space feels light and feathery for this turn and can ignore the effects of gravity for the rest of the turn.

cloudba.name: Large Cloud (Left)
cloudba.visual: light blue background with left half of cloud
cloudba.desc: A player who passes this space feels light and feathery for this turn and can ignore the effects of gravity for the rest of the turn.

cloudbb.name: Large Cloud (Right)
cloudbb.visual: light blue background with right half of cloud
cloudbb.desc: A player who passes this space feels light and feathery for this turn and can ignore the effects of gravity for the rest of the turn.

pipehdb.name: Sideways Warp Pipe
pipehdb.desc: Impassible. A player who ends their turn one space to the left or right of this one can choose to enter the pipe. The pipe leads to an unknown location.

pipehead.name: Warp Pipe
pipehead.desc: Impassible. A player who ends their turn one space above this one can choose to enter the pipe. The pipe leads to an unknown location.

qblock.name: ? Block
qblock.desc: Impassible. A player who ends their turn one space below this one can choose to hit the block, gaining either several yellow coins or a random useful item. If they do so, this space turns into a Used ? Block.

water.name: Water
water.desc: A player who moves onto this space must stop here. A player on a Water space is not subject to the effects of gravity.

blue.name: Blue Party!
blue.desc: A player who lands here gains 3 yellow coins. Instead of moving normally, a player on a Party! Space (or the Altar) can move one space along the highways connecting to their current space. A player cannot perform normal movement and Party! highway movement on the same turn. A player on this space is not affected by gravity.

red.name: Red Party!
red.desc: A player who lands here loses 3 yellow coins. Instead of moving normally, a player on a Party! Space (or the Altar) can move one space along the highways connecting to their current space. A player cannot perform normal movement and Party! highway movement on the same turn. A player on this space is not affected by gravity.

qparty.name: ? Party!
qparty.visual: green circular space containing question mark
qparty.desc: When a player lands here, something random will happen nearby. Instead of moving normally, a player on a Party! Space (or the Altar) can move one space along the highways connecting to their current space. A player cannot perform normal movement and Party! highway movement on the same turn. A player on this space is not affected by gravity.

bowser.name: Bowser Party!
bowser.desc: When a player lands here, something bad will happen to them. Instead of moving normally, a player on a Party! Space (or the Altar) can move one space along the highways connecting to their current space. A player cannot perform normal movement and Party! highway movement on the same turn. A player on this space is not affected by gravity.

dk.name: Donkey Kong Party!
dk.desc: When a player lands here, something good will happen to them. Instead of moving normally, a player on a Party! Space (or the Altar) can move one space along the highways connecting to their current space. A player cannot perform normal movement and Party! highway movement on the same turn. A player on this space is not affected by gravity.

bank.name: Koopa Bank Party!
bank.visual: blue circular space with bag of money on it
bank.desc: When a player other than the owner lands here, they must pay 5 coins to the bank. If the owner of this space lands here, they collect any coins that have accumulated on this space. Instead of moving normally, a player on a Party! Space (or the Altar) can move one space along the highways connecting to their current space. A player cannot perform normal movement and Party! highway movement on the same turn. A player on this space is not affected by gravity.

Instead of moving normally, a player on a Party! Space (or the Altar) can move one space along the highways connecting to their current space. A player cannot perform normal movement and Party! highway movement on the same turn. A player on this space is not affected by gravity.

xflip.name: Flipping Switch Space
xflip.visual: red blocky space with stuck out tongue
xflip.desc: A player who lands here can choose to enable or disable the game board mechanic of flipping the board horizontally every turn. Items such as the Vampire Mask can be used to move, even if the board doesn't move, when the flipping effect is disabled.

gravity.name: Gravity Switch Space
gravity.visual: green space with arrow switch panel
gravity.desc: A player who lands here can choose to change the direction of gravity to any of the four cardinal directions of their choosing.

oneupblock.name: Hidden 1-Up Block
oneupblock.desc: Behaves like a Blue Sky space normally. But if a player is ever on the space immediately below this one, then this space turns into a Used ? Block Space and gives that player a useful item.

cblock.name: Coin Block
cblock.desc: Impassible, and behaves like a Brick Block. If a player is ever on the space immediately below this one, then this space turns into a Used ? Block Space and gives that player ten yellow coins.

hqblock.name: Hidden ? Block
hqblock.desc: Impassible, and behaves like a Brick Block. If a player is ever on the space immediately below this one, then this space turns into a Used ? Block Space and gives that player a useful item.

twain.name: Mark Twain
twain.visual: digitally colored portrait of Mark Twain
twain.desc: A player who is on the same space as Mark Twain can direct him to sail to any Water Space which is reachable from his current position by traversing only Water Spaces. The player and anyone else on Mark Twain's space move with him when this happens. Moving in this way costs no movement points.

lava.name: Lava Space
lava.visual: dark red space with yellow spotty texture
lava.desc: Anyone who moves onto a Lava Space must stop on it, similar to water. Additionally, a player who touches a Lava Space for any reason takes 2 damage, unless they are lavaproof or are floating above the ground (e.g. via a Lakitu Cloud or a balloon). This space is unaffected by gravity.

lavashop.name: Lava Shop
lavashop.visual: dark red space with yellow spotty texture and white 'S'
lavashop.desc: A player who lands here gains a random, useful lava-related item. This counts as a shop for the purposes of the Parkour Shop, and this space does NOT inflict lava damage. This space is unaffected by gravity.

infinity.name: Infinity Space
infinity.visual: middle green space with sharp blue infinity sign
infinity.desc: This space has reached a point where time has no meaning. A player who lands on this space will feel an infinite length of time pass and will enter the realm of infinity. This space cannot be modified by other space effects.

partyplanner.name: Party Planner
partyplanner.desc: Single use. Select two Party! spaces and connect them via a new highway.

cappy.name: Cappy
cappy.desc: Can be thrown at an adjacent non-player token. That token ceases to be, and you acquire any abilities of that token. You may only copy the abilities of one token at a time, and you may choose to release your capture at any time (which causes the token to appear on a nearby space).

hammer.name: Super Hammer
hammer.desc: You may move onto Brick Block spaces. If you do so, the space is converted into a neutral space.

extradice.name: Extra Dice Block
extradice.desc: If you choose to move along Party! spaces, you may move an extra Party! space. You do not count as having landed on the first one.

encumber.name: Encumbering Stone
encumber.desc: At the start of your turn, rather than dropping one space due to gravity, you drop as far as you can until you hit the floor or a space that's not affected by gravity. You may not voluntarily drop or trade this item.

bankcap.name: Koopa Bank Capsule
bankcap.desc: Single use. Use this while standing on a Party! Space to turn that space into a Koopa Bank Party! Space belonging to you.

vampmask.name: Vampire Mask
vampmask.desc: You may choose to move with the board when it mirrors, even if you normally wouldn't.

carsponge.name: Car Sponge
carsponge.desc: Single use. On the turn you use this, any Water Spaces you move onto dry up and become neutral spaces. You are not forced to stop when this happens.

sabotagegun.name: Sabotage Gun
sabotagegun.desc: Each turn, you may name a player. That player's actions on THIS TURN are interpreted as the reverse of whatever they normally would be.

bananapeel.name: Banana Peel
bananapeel.desc: Put this on your current space or an adjacent space. A Banana Peel is a HIDDEN object. Next time someone passes that space, they trip over the Banana Peel, forcing them to stop on that space and take 1 damage. The Banana Peel is consumed after one such use. Banana Peels cannot be placed on Start or the Altar.

gavel.name: Gavel of Justice (2016)
gavel.desc: This item can be used once per turn. Select a non-player token on the same or an adjacent space. Over the next turn, all players will be allowed to vote on whether that token is guilty or innocent (a player can simply refuse to vote, which is different than an innocent vote). If the token gets more guilty votes than innocent ones, it is removed from the field at the end of that turn.

merctailor.name: Mercerenies the Tailor (2017)
merctailor.desc: As long as this item is in your inventory, it will happily make you custom-made suits. Once per turn, you can employ your private tailor to build you an article of clothing that will boost your stats by a small amount. If this item is ever dropped, Mercerenies gets to make his wish come true.

mecha.name: Mecha Bowser Suit (2018)
mecha.desc: Single use. When a player lands on a Bowser Space (or a variant thereof), you may use this item. Instead of Mercerenies, you get to select that player's punishment this turn. You may not use this to affect your own punishment.

transmog.name: Transmogrifier (2018 BR)
transmog.desc: You may transform the space you are on into any other type of space that already exists in the game. This item can be used once per turn.

neutralize.name: Neutralizing Beam (2020)
neutralize.desc: Single use. Every space (including any gaps) that is horizontally or vertically aligned with you is turned into a neutral space. Any players caught in the blast take 1 damage (mitigated by DEF) from the beam.

ghostpuppet.name: Ghost Puppet (2018 BR)
ghostpuppet.desc: You may summon a ghost on your current space at the start of your turn, if you don't already have a ghost in play. The ghost has MOV equal to your own, can move over gaps, and is under your control. The ghost has no HP and cannot attack or interact with the board in any way. On a later turn, you may jump to the space your ghost is on, which destroys the ghost and this item.

johnwick.name: John Wick Suit
johnwick.desc: A suit that exudes confidence and strength. +1 to the wearer's DEF, and the wearer has increased chance of succeeding at any activity that involves persuasion or charisma (such as telling Diddy Kong a good joke).

kocarina.name: Kokiri Ocarina
kocarina.desc: When this Ocarina is played, it summons Shaq to hold up the Moon, preventing it from crashing for 1 to 6 turns (at random, based on an IRL d6 roll). After being used, the Kokiri Ocarina moves to a random traversable space. If this item is in a player's inventory when the Moon hits, it leaves their inventory and moves to a random traversable space.

effects.name: Heavy
effects.desc: Every time you leave a space, there is a 10% chance of that space being destroyed, similar to a Crumbled Space.

item.name: Item
item.desc: Icon used to represent items on the map.

goldcoin.name: Gold Coin
goldcoin.desc: Can be picked up by a player. Always protected from wishes. Emits light level 1.

southghost.name: Southbridge's Ghost
southghost.desc: Southbridge's ghost, as summoned by the Ghost Puppet (2018 BR).

balloon.name: Balloon
balloon.desc: Moves up one to three spaces per turn, stopping if it encounters a player. Balloons can move freely over gaps and ignore gravity. A player on the same space as a Balloon can grab the Balloon, allowing them to ignore gravity for that turn. If they do so, the Balloon pops at the end of the turn. If a Balloon reaches the top of the board, or touches any spiky or sharp object, it also pops.

cake.name: Cake
cake.desc: A player on the same space as a Cake may choose to eat it. If they do so, the Cake is destroyed and the player becomes Heavy.

mermonkey.name: Mermonkey
mermonkey.desc: Moves randomly each turn, preferring to remain in water if possible. Mermonkey does not have to stop on Water spaces, but must stop moving if it passes a non-Water space. A player who lands on the same space as Mermonkey gains an item, as though they had landed on a Shop Space. Pops balloons on contact, and attacks any other non-player tokens.

goomba.name: Goomba
goomba.desc: Moves left or right each turn, continuing in one direction until forced to turn around. Can only be damaged by a player who moves onto the Goomba's space from above.

lcloud.name: Lakitu Cloud
lcloud.desc: Immune to gravity. A player on the same space as this cloud may choose to claim the cloud. For the rest of the turn, that player is immune to gravity and can ignore any movement penalties from spaces (including gaps). At the end of the turn, the cloud moves to a random position on the map.

ycoin.name: Yellow Coin
ycoin.desc: A yellow coin. Can be picked up and used as currency.

lavamonster.name: Lava Monster
lavamonster.desc: Lavaproof and cannot move outside of lava. Lava Monster normally remains stationary but will chase anyone who enters the same lava pool as itself. Lava Monster has two attacks but will only target players in its lava pool. First, it can throw lava rocks any distance horizontally or vertically, which hit the first player or token they encounter and deal 2 damage. Second, if Lava Monster occupies the same space as a player, it deals 5 damage to that player.

diddy.name: Diddy Kong
diddy.desc: A player who lands on the same space as Diddy Kong must tell him a joke. If Diddy laughs, he'll reward that player. If he doesn't, or if the player refuses to tell a joke, he'll chase them and shoot peanuts at them for the next few turns.

tele.name: Tele-rover
tele.desc: Moves diagonally each turn, continuing in the same direction as the previous turn if possible. A player or token on the same space as the Tele-rover can spend 2 movement points to instantly teleport to another Tele-rover on the board.

isfloor.name: Floor
isfloor.desc: There is nothing below this space, so it counts as a floor for gravity purposes.

goombacap.name: Goomba
goombacap.desc: You may only be damaged by players who collide with you from above. You do not slip on alternative terrain, such as ice. If you collide with another Goomba, you leap atop his head and form a Goomba stack.

rulings.desc: Any Altar wishes occur at the end of the turn, after all player movement is completed.
Effects which target a stat that a token lacks have no effect on the token. For example, a space that deals damage will not affect a token who has no concept of HP.

The specific nature of combat in the case of tokens which are deficient in some stats is this. All involved players or tokens who have an ATK stat will attack all involved players or tokens who have an HP stat. All such attacks happen simultaneously, and in general a token will never attack itself unless otherwise stated.

In general, an action which attempts to move into a gap is considered to be a mistake or a typo, and the player will not be allowed to move into the gap. If the movement into the gap was intentional, this should be specified in the post. This ruling does not apply if the player in question has any equipment that would enable him or her to pass the gaps without the normal penalty.

The larger the magnitude of a wish, the less likely it is to end up in the wisher's favor. That is, a simple wish is likely to go exactly as intended. A large and complicated wish may be interpreted extremely literally and the results may not be what was desired.
